>how did you find out about /hmofa/
It all started when I was browsing /b/ cuz bored. I came across a thread about those yinglet things from that webcomic Out of Placers and I thought they were interesting so I looked for the comic and found the author's website. It was alright so I read through the whole thing. When comic #50 came out(May 15, 2017) some anon(literally) in the comments posted about making a thread on /co/ which obviously got immediately nuked. That's when Val(the comic author) pointed out the only board to make the threads was /trash/ and another anon(literally again) posted pic related. For a while I would jump on the Oops thread when a new comic page came out. But soon after as popularity grew, the threads started to become too gay to endure and I got bored with the comic and just started browsing the catalog.

The first /hmofa/ thread I looked in was #12 and the lack of image content bored me so I left(wasnt really into reading at the time). The first story I actually read was something on Sofurry about a human male who was taken as a slave by a fox anthro after humans lost a war with interdimensional beings. They later fell in love and had kids I think(If anyone knows this story remind me the name). After finishing the story I realized reading about this shit was pretty cash money and wanted more so that brought me crawling back to /hmofa/ on a thread somewhere in the 20s(27 pretty sure). the OP image was gift.jpg if anyone knows that one. I started reading Femme Fatale and Chubby Cheetah and got hooked on reading. Ever since then /hmofa/ has been the first tab in my browser all the way up until now.

TL:DR - The chain of events that brought me here started with a Yinglet thread on /b/. And I've been here since May of 2017 (somewhere around thread #27)

And before you say it. No. I do not follow Out of Placers anymore. The author got way too obsessed with transformation and it got weird.
